21.title: Oh Romeo
21.plot: Patterson High has chosen to put on the production of Romeo and Juliet. At first, Jonesy thinks Shakespeare is "boring", but when he hears that Amber is in the running to play Juliet, because "she gets the lead role in every production"; Jonesy then signs up to play Romeo. But between Jonesy and Amber; things get a little awkward when they find out that Romeo and Juliet have to kiss; so they think of a way to stop that from happening, even if it means having garlic bread for lunch.

imdb.plot outline: "As the Bell Rings" focuses on the break time antics of the 6 key characters. The action takes place in a school corridor, just outside the head teacher's office and the window into their world is literally the window of the school building. The stars of 'As the Bell rings' use their break time to come up various schemes from winning a date with the prettiest girl in school to trying to captain every school club or team.
